- Use metadata Title only<br/></span>Write Title from ComicInfo.xml or other embedded metadata.</p></body></html>\", None))\n+        self.spreadShiftBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Shift first page to opposite side in landscape for two page spread alignment\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.metadataTitleBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Metadata Title\", None))\n+        self.spreadShiftBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Spread shift\", None))\n #if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.mozJpegBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Unchecked - JPEG<br/></span>Use JPEG files</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Indeterminate - force PNG<br/></span>Create PNG files instead JPEG</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Checked - mozJpeg<br/></span>10-20% smaller JPEG file, with the same image quality, but processing time multiplied by 2</p></body></html>\", None))\n+        self.fileFusionBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p>Combines all selected files into a single file. (Helpful for combining chapters into volumes.)</p></body></html>\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.mozJpegBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"JPEG/PNG/mozJpeg\", None))\n+        self.fileFusionBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"File Fusion\", None))\n #if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.autoLevelBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p>By default, KCC maps the darkest pixel value to pure black (the black point.)</p><p>Extreme black point sets the black point to be the most common dark pixel value.</p><p>Useful when text is black but artwork is gray.</p></body></html>\", None))\n+        self.colorBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p style='white-space:pre'>Disable conversion to grayscale.</p></body></html>\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.autoLevelBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Extreme Black Point\", None))\n+        self.colorBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Color mode\", None))\n #if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.autocontrastBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Unchecked - BW only<br/></span>Only autocontrast bw pages. Ignored for pages where near blacks or whites don't exist.</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Indeterminate - Disabled<br/></span>Disable autocontrast</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Checked - BW and Color<br/></span>BW and color images will be autocontrasted. Ignored for pages where near blacks or whites don't exist.</p></body></html>\", None))\n+        self.croppingBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Unchecked - Disabled</span></p><p>Disabled</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Indeterminate - Margins<br/></span>Margins</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Checked - Margins + page numbers<br/></span>Margins +page numbers</p></body></html>\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.autocontrastBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Autocontrast\", None))\n+        self.croppingBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Cropping mode\", None))\n #if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.defaultOutputFolderBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Unchecked - next to source<br/></span>Place output files next to source files</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Indeterminate - folder next to source<br/></span>Place output files in a folder next to source files</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Checked - Custom<br/></span>Place output files in custom directory specified by right button</p></body></html>\", None))\n+        self.webtoonBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p style='white-space:pre'>Enable special parsing mode for Korean Webtoons.</p></body></html>\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.defaultOutputFolderBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Output Folder\", None))\n+        self.webtoonBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Webtoon mode\", None))\n #if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.defaultOutputFolderButton.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p>Use this to select the default output directory.</p></body></html>\", None))\n+        self.disableProcessingBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p style='white-space:pre'>Do not process any image, ignore profile and processing options.</p></body></html>\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.defaultOutputFolderButton.setText(\"\")\n+        self.disableProcessingBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Disable processing\", None))\n #if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.jpegQualityBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"The JPEG quality, on a scale from 0 (worst) to 95 (best). \\n\"\n-\"\\n\"\n-\"Default is 85 for most devices besides Kindle Scribe and Colorsoft, which are 90.\\n\"\n-\"\\n\"\n-\"Higher values are larger and higher quality, and may resolve blank page issues.\", None))\n+        self.mangaBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p style='white-space:pre'>Enable right-to-left reading.</p></body></html>\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.jpegQualityBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Custom JPEG Quality\", None))\n+        self.mangaBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Right-to-left (manga)\", None))\n #if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.pdfExtractBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Use the PDF image extraction method from KCC 8 and earlier.\\n\"\n-\"\\n\"\n-\"Useful for really weird PDFs.\", None))\n+        self.maximizeStrips.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"<html><head/><body><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Unchecked - 1x4<br/></span>Keep format 1x4 panels strips.</p><p><span style=\\\" font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\\\">Checked - 2x2<br/></span>Turn 1x4 strips to 2x2 to maximize screen usage.</p></body></html>\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.pdfExtractBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"PDF Legacy Extract\", None))\n+        self.maximizeStrips.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"1x4 to 2x2 strips\", None))\n #if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.coverFillBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Resize cover to exact device resolution by center-cropping to aspect ratio first.\\n\"\n-\"May crop top/bottom or left/right depending on source aspect ratio. Not implemented for Kindle Scribe.\", None))\n+        self.rotateRightBox.setToolTip(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Rotate 2 page spreads in opposite direction than normal.\", None))\n #endif // QT_CONFIG(tooltip)\n-        self.coverFillBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Cover Fill\", None))\n+        self.rotateRightBox.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Rotate Right\", None))\n         self.gammaLabel.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"Gamma: Auto\", None))\n         self.jpegQualityLabel.setText(QCoreApplication.translate(\"mainWindow\", u\"JPEG Quality:\", None))\n     # retranslateUi\ndiff --git a/kindlecomicconverter/comic2ebook.py b/kindlecomicconverter/comic2ebook.py\nindex 30c99c61..1cfc5c94 100755\n--- a/kindlecomicconverter/comic2ebook.py\n+++ b/kindlecomicconverter/comic2ebook.py\n@@ -1356,6 +1356,8 @@ def makeParser():\n                                 help=\"Shift first page to opposite side in landscape for spread alignment\")\n     output_options.add_argument(\"--norotate\", action=\"store_true\", dest=\"norotate\", default=False,\n                                 help=\"Do not rotate double page spreads in spread splitter option.\")\n+    output_options.add_argument(\"--rotateright\", action=\"store_true\", dest=\"rotateright\", default=False,\n+                                help=\"Rotate double page spreads in opposite direction.\")\n     output_options.add_argument(\"--rotatefirst\", action=\"store_true\", dest=\"rotatefirst\", default=False,\n                                 help=\"Put rotated 2 page spread first in spread splitter option.\")\n \ndiff --git a/kindlecomicconverter/image.py b/kindlecomicconverter/image.py\nindex 3341940d..635886fb 100755\n--- a/kindlecomicconverter/image.py\n+++ b/kindlecomicconverter/image.py\n@@ -197,7 +197,10 @@ def splitCheck(self):\n                 and not self.opt.webtoon and self.opt.splitter == 1:\n             spread = self.image\n             if not self.opt.norotate:\n-                spread = spread.rotate(90, Image.Resampling.BICUBIC, True)\n+                if not self.opt.rotateright:\n+                    spread = spread.rotate(90, Image.Resampling.BICUBIC, True)\n+                else:\n+                    spread = spread.rotate(-90, Image.Resampling.BICUBIC, True)\n             self.payload.append(['R', self.source, spread, self.fill])\n         elif (width > height) != (dstwidth > dstheight) and not self.opt.webtoon:\n             if self.opt.splitter != 1:\n@@ -218,7 +221,10 @@ def splitCheck(self):\n             if self.opt.splitter > 0:\n                 spread = self.image\n                 if not self.opt.norotate:\n-                    spread = spread.rotate(90, Image.Resampling.BICUBIC, True)\n+                    if not self.opt.rotateright:\n+                        spread = spread.rotate(90, Image.Resampling.BICUBIC, True)\n+                    else:\n+                        spread = spread.rotate(-90, Image.Resampling.BICUBIC, True)\n                 self.payload.append(['R', self.source, spread, self.fill])\n         else:\n             self.payload.append(['N', self.source, self.image, self.fill])\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Feature Request] Allow double spread page to rotate in selected direction\nIf this is vague allow me to explain, currently when selecting the option to rotate and spread double page it will always rotate in +90 degree, some device cover tend work in favor while others don't like me for example and allowing the rotation to opposite, as in -90 degree, would be a quality of life for some people\n\nFor the time being I am going to flip them manually but if we can have this it might be of useful quality of life in the future\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "@AVM-1996 Done, will be included in next release.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc/commit/8c2b898afa1c709667e1e9ae57d6529f6bc5489c"], "created_at": "2026-03-13T21:13:53Z"}
{"repo": "ciromattia/kcc", "pull_number": 1055, "instance_id": "ciromattia__kcc-1055", "issue_numbers": [891], "base_commit": "9a605c2d8ad5d15b3a6bc9ebda1d0647a4e11a23", "patch": "diff --git a/.github/workflows/package-osx-legacy.yml b/.github/workflows/package-osx-legacy.yml\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 00000000..304f404a\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/.github/workflows/package-osx-legacy.yml\n@@ -0,0 +1,66 @@\n+name: build KCC for osx legacy\n+\n+on:\n+  workflow_dispatch:\n+  push:\n+    tags:\n+      - \"v*.*.*\"\n+\n+    # Don't trigger if it's just a documentation update\n+    paths-ignore:\n+      - '**.md'\n+      - '**.MD'\n+      - '**.yml'\n+      - '**.sh'\n+      - 'docs/**'\n+      - 'Dockerfile'\n+      - 'LICENSE'\n+      - '.gitattributes'\n+      - '.gitignore'\n+      - '.dockerignore'\n+\n+jobs:\n+  build:\n+    strategy:\n+      matrix:\n+        os: [ macos-13 ]\n+    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}\n+    env:\n+      # We need the official Python, because the GA ones only support newer macOS versions\n+      # The deployment target is picked up by the Python build tools automatically\n+      PYTHON_VERSION: 3.11.9\n+      MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET: '10.13'\n+    steps:\n+      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n+      - name: Get Python\n+        run: curl https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.11.9/python-3.11.9-macos11.pkg -o \"python.pkg\"\n+      - name: Install Python\n+        run: |\n+          sudo installer -pkg python.pkg -target /\n+      - name: Install Python dependencies\n+        run: |\n+          python3 --version\n+          pip3 install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel pyinstaller certifi\n+          pip3 install --upgrade -r requirements-osx-legacy.txt\n+          ./gen_ui_files.sh\n+      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n+        with:\n+          node-version: 16\n+      - run: npm install -g appdmg\n+      - name: build binary\n+        run: |\n+          python3 setup.py build_binary\n+      - name: upload build\n+        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n+        with:\n+          name: osx-build-${{ runner.arch }}\n+          path: dist/*.dmg\n+      - name: Release\n+        uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v2\n+        if: startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/')\n+        with:\n+          prerelease: true\n+          generate_release_notes: true\n+          files: |\n+            LICENSE.txt\n+            dist/*.dmg\ndiff --git a/requirements-osx-legacy.txt b/requirements-osx-legacy.txt\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 00000000..018a6005\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/requirements-osx-legacy.txt\n@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@\n+PySide6==6.5.2\n+Pillow>=11.3.0\n+psutil>=5.9.5\n+requests>=2.31.0\n+python-slugify>=1.2.1\n+raven>=6.0.0\n+packaging>=23.2\n+mozjpeg-lossless-optimization>=1.2.0\n+natsort>=8.4.0\n+distro>=1.8.0\n+numpy<2\n+PyMuPDF>=1.26.1\ndiff --git a/setup.py b/setup.py\nindex 34f5652b..0b14e7ed 100644\n--- a/setup.py\n+++ b/setup.py\n@@ -38,7 +38,10 @@ def run(self):\n         if sys.platform == 'darwin':\n             os.system('pyinstaller --hidden-import=_cffi_backend -y -D -i icons/comic2ebook.icns -n \"Kindle Comic Converter\" -w -s kcc.py')\n             # TODO /usr/bin/codesign --force -s \"$MACOS_CERTIFICATE_NAME\" --options runtime dist/Applications/Kindle\\ Comic\\ Converter.app -v\n-            os.system(f'appdmg kcc.json dist/kcc_macos_{platform.processor()}_{VERSION}.dmg')\n+            if os.getenv('MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET') == '10.13':\n+                os.system(f'appdmg kcc.json dist/kcc_osx_10_13_legacy_{VERSION}.dmg')\n+            else:\n+                os.system(f'appdmg kcc.json dist/kcc_macos_{platform.processor()}_{VERSION}.dmg')\n             sys.exit(0)\n         elif sys.platform == 'win32':\n             os.system('pyinstaller --hidden-import=_cffi_backend -y -F -i icons\\\\comic2ebook.ico -n KCC_' + VERSION + ' -w --noupx kcc.py')\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "macos-11 Big Sur Refuses to open KCC\nHi, I'm trying to install and open KCC for the first time.\n\nI am able to install but it refuses to open.\n\nI have attached screenshot of error that comes up and the specs of my Mac.\n\nAny solutions would be appreciated.\n\nMbp 2013\n\n<img width=\"847\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/84a2e8ef-9b2d-4f0d-89b2-eccc861cd7fd\" />\n", "hints_text": "@miayoung969 \n\nTry the kcc_macos_i386 and:\n\n1) ~v7.0.0 this was built on macos-12. Future versions were built on macos-13 due to GitHub removing macos-12 build machines. It's not guaranteed that apps build on newer macOS run on older ones.~\n2) install from source following readme instructions. May not work. \n3) install at least macos-12 using open core legacy patcher. Macos-13 os probably possible too. \n4) ~maybe the windows 7 build. It has a macOS version there too but very old~\n\nhttps://github.com/ciromattia/kcc?tab=readme-ov-file#install-from-source\n@miayoung969 @Majorfi Are you still interested in Big Sur build of KCC?\nYes please \n@miayoung969 @Majorfi\n\nI'll be creating test builds here. Let me know if any of them work:\n\nMy intention is for macos 10.13 compatilbilty. Here are some attempts where I continually downgrade things.\n\nPython 3.9 only:\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16554710428\n\n+Downgraded pyside6:\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16554784536\n\n+rebuilt pyside6\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16586230194\n\n+downgrade numpy\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16586288835\n\nIf they work I'll optimize the speed further. \n\nEDIT: \n\nPython 3.11 may have better compatbility actually...\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16613455914\nthank you @axu2 I have installed the Python 3.11 link. \n\nthe app opens but its not converting. it keeps saying extraction failed \n\n<img width=\"725\" height=\"672\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/46f73b1e-573e-4e00-bdf0-d6b17109fd15\" />\n\nI have installed macOS 7-Zip/Unar via Homebrew as instructed here - https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc/wiki/Installation#7-zip\nI have also installed kindle previewer 3 as instructed under PREREQUISITES here - https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc#7-zip\nmy input format is CBZ\nis there anything else I should/need to download/install?\n(please note I've blacked out my source, its not empty)\nThat's amazing that it runs, thanks for confirming! \n\nKindle Previewer is not needed since you are using a Kobo.\n\n~Which Mac are you using? And which macOS version?~ Nevermind you said MBP 2013 macOS 11 earlier.\n\nHave you tried restarting your Mac?\n\nThat error message indicates that it can't see your sevenzip or unar. \n\nCan you please open a terminal window and tell me what happens when you type each of these lines and click enter each time\n\n@miayoung969 \n\n```\nunar\n7zz\nwhich unar\nwhich 7zz\n```\n\nTemporary workaround would be to install `The Unarchiver` to extract your CBZ to a folder outside of KCC. Then use the extracted folder directly in KCC. But ideally KCC would detect `unar` and `7zz` so that isn't needed.\n@miayoung969 Looks like homebrew won't let you install either on older macOS versions.\n\nIn that case, you may need to download unar and 7zz manually:\n\nhttps://7-zip.org/download.html\nhttps://theunarchiver.com/command-line\n\nAnd copy the `7zz` and `unar` binary files to `/usr/bin/local`\n\n~EDIT:~\n\n~I also got a request for a macos 10.10 build. This may work.~\n~https://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16663974580~\n@axu2 I think I've installed those and its kind working. But when I go to convert I get the following error: \n\nError during conversion /Users/Blank/Downloads/Complete/Who Made Me a Princess (Digital 2017 Tappytoon)/Who Made Me a Princess S1 Chapter 002.zip:\n\n(\"One of workers crashed. Cause: cannot identify image file '/Users/Blank/Downloads/Complete/Who Made Me a Princess (Digital 2017 Tappytoon)/KCC-uo32pzm_-Splitted/.DS_Store'\", '  File \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2panel.py\", line 102, in splitImage\\n  File \"PIL/Image.py\", line 3580, in open\\n')\n\nTraceback:\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/KCC_gui.py\", line 334, in run\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2ebook.py\", line 1491, in makeBook\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2panel.py\", line 277, in main\n@miayoung969 If possible, provide a test file and the settings you used in a screenshot.\n\nDoes the error occur when converting in normal mode, not webtoon mode?\n\nAlso, what's the result of \n\nunar\n7zz\nwhich unar\nwhich 7zz\n\nAre you doing anything special, like an external drive or network drive?\nLast login: Fri Aug  1 12:55:48 on ttys000\nBlank@ Blank-MBP ~ % unar\nzsh: command not found: unar\nBlank@ Blank-MBP ~ % 7zz\n\n7-Zip (z) 25.00 (x64) : Copyright (c) 1999-2025 Igor Pavlov : 2025-07-05\n 64-bit locale=en_GB.UTF-8 Threads:4 OPEN_MAX:256\n\nUsage: 7zz <command> [<switches>...] <archive_name> [<file_names>...] [@listfile]\n\n<Commands>\n  a : Add files to archive\n  b : Benchmark\n  d : Delete files from archive\n  e : Extract files from archive (without using directory names)\n  h : Calculate hash values for files\n  i : Show information about supported formats\n  l : List contents of archive\n  rn : Rename files in archive\n  t : Test integrity of archive\n  u : Update files to archive\n  x : eXtract files with full paths\n\n<Switches>\n  -- : Stop switches and @listfile parsing\n  -ai[r[-|0]][m[-|2]][w[-]]{@listfile|!wildcard} : Include archives\n  -ax[r[-|0]][m[-|2]][w[-]]{@listfile|!wildcard} : eXclude archives\n  -ao{a|s|t|u} : set Overwrite mode\n  -an : disable archive_name field\n  -bb[0-3] : set output log level\n  -bd : disable progress indicator\n  -bs{o|e|p}{0|1|2} : set output stream for output/error/progress line\n  -bt : show execution time statistics\n  -i[r[-|0]][m[-|2]][w[-]]{@listfile|!wildcard} : Include filenames\n  -m{Parameters} : set compression Method\n    -mmt[N] : set number of CPU threads\n    -mx[N] : set compression level: -mx1 (fastest) ... -mx9 (ultra)\n  -o{Directory} : set Output directory\n  -p{Password} : set Password\n  -r[-|0] : Recurse subdirectories for name search\n  -sa{a|e|s} : set Archive name mode\n  -scc{UTF-8|WIN|DOS} : set charset for console input/output\n  -scs{UTF-8|UTF-16LE|UTF-16BE|WIN|DOS|{id}} : set charset for list files\n  -scrc[CRC32|CRC64|SHA256|SHA1|XXH64|BLAKE2SP|*] : set hash function for x, e, h commands\n  -sdel : delete files after compression\n  -seml[.] : send archive by email\n  -sfx[{name}] : Create SFX archive\n  -si[{name}] : read data from stdin\n  -slp : set Large Pages mode\n  -slt : show technical information for l (List) command\n  -snh : store hard links as links\n  -snl : store symbolic links as links\n  -sni : store NT security information\n  -sns[-] : store NTFS alternate streams\n  -so : write data to stdout\n  -spd : disable wildcard matching for file names\n  -spe : eliminate duplication of root folder for extract command\n  -spf[2] : use fully qualified file paths\n  -ssc[-] : set sensitive case mode\n  -sse : stop archive creating, if it can't open some input file\n  -ssp : do not change Last Access Time of source files while archiving\n  -ssw : compress shared files\n  -stl : set archive timestamp from the most recently modified file\n  -stm{HexMask} : set CPU thread affinity mask (hexadecimal number)\n  -stx{Type} : exclude archive type\n  -t{Type} : Set type of archive\n  -u[-][p#][q#][r#][x#][y#][z#][!newArchiveName] : Update options\n  -v{Size}[b|k|m|g] : Create volumes\n  -w[{path}] : assign Work directory. Empty path means a temporary directory\n  -x[r[-|0]][m[-|2]][w[-]]{@listfile|!wildcard} : eXclude filenames\n  -y : assume Yes on all queries\nBlank@ Blank-MBP ~ % which unar\nunar not found\nBlank@ Blank-MBP ~ % which 7zz\n/usr/local/bin/7zz\nBlank@ Blank-MBP ~ % \n\nIt looks like you didn't copy `unar` to `usr/bin/local`.\n\nThere are two versions, if the first version of unar doesn't work, try the legacy version.\n@axu2  out of webtoon mode it converts but to jpg? I want it to convert to one combined epub\n\n<img width=\"1362\" height=\"1256\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/908967a2-f7c1-4748-80b6-f9dfe78d5e1d\" />\n\n<img width=\"1032\" height=\"604\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b0e6dba8-a787-4957-8f89-9305e515941c\" />\n\nAre you sure that's just not a leftover file from something else? The epub should be around there.\n\nTry partially checking the Output folder box.\n\nAnd please fully read prior messages. If you prefer message SpecOps on the KCC discord.\nMaybe `7zz` doesn't work right on older macOS.\n\nMaybe remove 7zz from /usr/bin/local\n\nOpen a terminal and `open /usr/bin/local`\n\nThen delete `7zz` from the finder window.\n\nThen drag and drop the legacy version of `unar` into there if the normal one doesn't run when you type `unar`.\n\n<img width=\"518\" height=\"241\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4547a6e1-ab85-4abc-b1bf-d5c0218f4497\" />\nI think that's now working. Thank you for your help.\n@miayoung969 Can you provide details about what went wrong and how you fixed for future users? \n@axu2  you were correct, the epub was being put in a random place. I changed the output/searched the file fore pub and found it.\n\n\nDoes your original issue occur with the webtoon box checked? Can you please provide test file? I am assuming only difference is webtoon box check. @miayoung969 \nI think there might be an issue with one of my files. Its converted all of S1 of the comic fine but during S2 it keeps coming up with this error: \n\nError during conversion /Users/Blank/Downloads/Complete/Who Made Me a Princess (Digital 2017 Tappytoon)/Who Made Me a Princess S2 Chapter 060.zip:\n\n(\"One of workers crashed. Cause: cannot identify image file '/Users/Blank/Downloads/Complete/Who Made Me a Princess (Digital 2017 Tappytoon)/KCC-aqhnc87k-Splitted/OEBPS/.DS_Store'\", '  File \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2panel.py\", line 102, in splitImage\\n  File \"PIL/Image.py\", line 3580, in open\\n')\n\nTraceback:\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/KCC_gui.py\", line 334, in run\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2ebook.py\", line 1491, in makeBook\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2panel.py\", line 277, in main\n\n> Its converted all of S1 of the comic fine\n\nBut your prior message had error:\n\n> Error during conversion /Users/Blank/Downloads/Complete/Who Made Me a Princess (Digital 2017 Tappytoon)/Who Made Me a Princess S1 Chapter 002.zip:\n\nAnyways, it's hard to debug this without a test zip file and the exact settings you used. \n\nOr drop it into this drive: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1zl5I0aIz6onSx1vW72qaAWRLD6Nnev9g?usp=sharing\n\nOr share it however you prefer.\n\n@miayoung969 \n@axu2 sorry I actually deleted the file when it didn't work. but I have another manga that has the same issue. would you still want me to upload the new file from the new manga that has the same issue?\n@miayoung969 send me a file and the exact settings you used to get the error. \n\nId prefer that 5 mb file\n@axu2 I'm sorry, I no longer have access to the 5mb file.\n\nI have uploaded the new file into the google drive.\n\nit gives me the same error. here is the error and the settings:\n\n<img width=\"981\" height=\"608\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/02fffabe-7b7e-4c29-bbb2-4aea2286b0cf\" />\n\nFully error message:\nError during conversion /Volumes/My Passport for Mac/Books/Manga/Into the Light, Once Again (2021) (Digital) (Dalte)/Into the Light, Once Again c001 (2021) (Digital) (Dalte).cbz:\n\n(\"One of workers crashed. Cause: cannot identify image file '/Volumes/My Passport for Mac/Books/Manga/Into the Light, Once Again (2021) (Digital) (Dalte)/KCC-c9ckakqw-Splitted/OEBPS/.DS_Store'\", '  File \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2panel.py\", line 102, in splitImage\\n  File \"PIL/Image.py\", line 3580, in open\\n')\n\nTraceback:\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/KCC_gui.py\", line 334, in run\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2ebook.py\", line 1491, in makeBook\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2panel.py\", line 277, in main\n\nInteresting. \n\nCan you provide the Get Info of your external drive? Should look like this:\n\n<img width=\"254\" height=\"208\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5b3e0dd0-6c36-4afb-ac27-3f7e6903a156\" />\n\nThe conversion might work if you convert on your main internal drive instead of external.\n\nMy hypothesis is that macOS 11 is adding a .DS_Store for some reason (possible a bug)\n<img width=\"512\" height=\"958\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b1b207b5-f8bc-4d2c-8fec-6ef1825a1430\" />\n\nPreviously I was converting files on my internal drive. The \"Who made me a princess\" one. \nOh I see. \n\nCan you tell me if your main internal drive is apfs or macos extended?\nHow do I check? \ud83d\ude05\nThis build might work:\n\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16688198447\n\n@miayoung969 \n\nCheck in Disk Utility:\n\n<img width=\"577\" height=\"152\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/97bb3788-df71-4d58-ab62-0740e2d46be0\" />\ninternal drive is apfs\n\nAPFS System Snapshot \u2022 APFS (Encrypted)\n103GB free storage \nHmmm ok, at this point I'm thinking that this is a macos-11 quirk, but I think I fixed it in above build. I'll need to make the code more resiliant to handle arbitrary cases.\n\n@miayoung969 Let me know if the build fixes your issue\n@axu2 I think I've been too ambitious. I've installed that latest build. But ticked webtoon mode and file fushion. had this error \n\nError during conversion /Volumes/My Passport for Mac/Books/Manga/Into the Light, Once Again (2021) (Digital) (Dalte)/Into the Light, Once Again c001 (2021) (Digital) (Dalte) [fused]:\n\n[Errno 66] Directory not empty: 'Images'\n\nTraceback:\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/KCC_gui.py\", line 334, in run\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2ebook.py\", line 1484, in makeBook\nFile \"kindlecomicconverter/comic2panel.py\", line 282, in main\nFile \"shutil.py\", line 752, in rmtree\nFile \"shutil.py\", line 672, in _rmtree_safe_fd\nFile \"shutil.py\", line 683, in _rmtree_safe_fd\nFile \"shutil.py\", line 681, in _rmtree_safe_fd\nOk I'll look into the new issue, but is the old issue gone? @miayoung969 \nYes, I think old issue is resolved. Thank you \nIn the meantime you can try using the old method of file fusion, you may need to install https://theunarchiver.com/ (I prefer the app store version) :\n\n- https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc/issues/612#issuecomment-2117985011\n@miayoung969 Can you upload a set of files that you tried fusing with their exact settings but got error? Ideally, it would only be two files.\n\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "@miayoung969 \n\nTry the kcc_macos_i386 and:\n\n1) ~v7.0.0 this was built on macos-12. Future versions were built on macos-13 due to GitHub removing macos-12 build machines. It's not guaranteed that apps build on newer macOS run on older ones.~\n2) install from source following readme instructions. May not work. \n3) install at least macos-12 using open core legacy patcher. Macos-13 os probably possible too. \n4) ~maybe the windows 7 build. It has a macOS version there too but very old~\n\nhttps://github.com/ciromattia/kcc?tab=readme-ov-file#install-from-source\n@miayoung969 @Majorfi Are you still interested in Big Sur build of KCC?\nYes please \n@miayoung969 @Majorfi\n\nI'll be creating test builds here. Let me know if any of them work:\n\nMy intention is for macos 10.13 compatilbilty. Here are some attempts where I continually downgrade things.\n\nPython 3.9 only:\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16554710428\n\n+Downgraded pyside6:\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16554784536\n\n+rebuilt pyside6\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16586230194\n\n+downgrade numpy\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16586288835\n\nIf they work I'll optimize the speed further. \n\nEDIT: \n\nPython 3.11 may have better compatbility actually...\nhttps://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16613455914\nthank you @axu2 I have installed the Python 3.11 link. \n\nthe app opens but its not converting. it keeps saying extraction failed \n\n<img width=\"725\" height=\"672\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/46f73b1e-573e-4e00-bdf0-d6b17109fd15\" />\n\nI have installed macOS 7-Zip/Unar via Homebrew as instructed here - https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc/wiki/Installation#7-zip\nI have also installed kindle previewer 3 as instructed under PREREQUISITES here - https://github.com/ciromattia/kcc#7-zip\nmy input format is CBZ\nis there anything else I should/need to download/install?\n(please note I've blacked out my source, its not empty)\nThat's amazing that it runs, thanks for confirming! \n\nKindle Previewer is not needed since you are using a Kobo.\n\n~Which Mac are you using? And which macOS version?~ Nevermind you said MBP 2013 macOS 11 earlier.\n\nHave you tried restarting your Mac?\n\nThat error message indicates that it can't see your sevenzip or unar. \n\nCan you please open a terminal window and tell me what happens when you type each of these lines and click enter each time\n\n@miayoung969 \n\n```\nunar\n7zz\nwhich unar\nwhich 7zz\n```\n\nTemporary workaround would be to install `The Unarchiver` to extract your CBZ to a folder outside of KCC. Then use the extracted folder directly in KCC. But ideally KCC would detect `unar` and `7zz` so that isn't needed.\n@miayoung969 Looks like homebrew won't let you install either on older macOS versions.\n\nIn that case, you may need to download unar and 7zz manually:\n\nhttps://7-zip.org/download.html\nhttps://theunarchiver.com/command-line\n\nAnd copy the `7zz` and `unar` binary files to `/usr/bin/local`\n\n~EDIT:~\n\n~I also got a request for a macos 10.10 build. This may work.~\n~https://github.com/axu2/kcc/actions/runs/16663974580~\n@axu2 I think I've installed those and its kind working. 